      "id": "checking_mt_oil",
      "title": "Checking M/T Oil",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "text": "Check for oil leaks.",
          "figure_ref": "fig3",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "text": "Check oil level.",
          "figure_ref": "fig4",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "Never start engine while checking oil level. Make sure the car is parked level. Check the oil level through speedometer cable hole. Use a straight wire or small ruler to measure the oil level from the top of the hole. The level should be in between \"H\" and \"L\". If topping up is required, add oil until \"H\"."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
